  "public_note": "Spiced blackberry mead with lemon",
  "private_note": "Recipe adapted from blackberry-mead.json based on available ingredients:\n- Scaled to 95% to fit fermenter volume\n- Water: 3.61L (95% of original 3.80L)\n- Honey: 1258g (92.5% of original 1360g)\n- Blackberries: 1075g (93.5% of original 1150g)\n- Yeast: Mangrove Jack's Mead Yeast M05 (substitute for Lalvin D-47) - higher attenuation (95-100% vs 77%), will ferment drier\n- Nutrient: Mangrove Jack Yeast Nutrient (substitute for Fermaid O) - 2g staggered additions\n- No Go-Ferm available - rehydrate yeast in plain water\n- Pectic Enzyme optional (may purchase before brewing)\n\nOriginal recipe from Reddit r/mead: https://www.reddit.com/r/mead/comments/1exv97k/blackberry_mead_recipe_check/\n\nHot water infusion with spices and lemon, poured over mashed berries. Pectic enzyme added before yeast pitch if available. Staggered nutrient additions (24h, 48h, 72h, 1 week). Degas daily to prevent mold on fruit. Rack through cheesecloth after 1 week to remove fruit.",
